{"_response_info":{"status":"ok"},"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/calculate-tax-on-company-cars.json","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/calculate-tax-on-company-cars","title":"Calculate tax on company cars","format":"answer","updated_at":"2013-01-10T16:59:07+00:00","details":{"need_id":"B704","business_proposition":true,"description":"As an employer, if you provide company cars or fuel for your employees' private use, you'll need to work out the taxable value so you can report this to HMRC.","language":"en","body":"\n<div class=\"summary\">\n<p>As an employer, if you provide company cars or fuel for your employees’ private use, you’ll need to work out the taxable value so you can report this to <abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr>.</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>You can do this by using:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li><abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr>&rsquo;s <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/calcs/cars.htm\" title=\"company car and car fuel benefit calculator\">company car and car fuel benefit calculator</a></li>\n  <li>commercial payroll software</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>Find out about <a href=\"/tax-company-benefits/tax-on-company-cars\" title=\"Tax on company benefits: Company cars\">tax on company cars if you’re an employee</a>.</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>You can also work out the value manually on <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://search2.hmrc.gov.uk/kb5/hmrc/forms/view.page?record=QD3XDgv9U1E&amp;formid=748\" title=\"P11D working sheet 2\">P11D working sheet 2.</a> You&rsquo;ll have to use this method if both of the following apply during the tax year you&rsquo;re reporting on:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>the car was unavailable for at least 30 consecutive days</li>\n  <li>you were providing fuel for private use, but stopped doing this</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Taxable value</h2>\n\n<p>The taxable value of a car is not the same as its cost. The taxable value also depends on:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>the amount of time the car is available during the tax year</li>\n  <li>the car&rsquo;s fuel type and level of CO2 emissions</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>‘Private use’ includes employees’ journeys between home and work, unless they’re travelling to a temporary place of work.</p>\n</div>\n\n","alternative_title":"Company car and fuel benefit calculator"},"tags":[{"title":"Payroll","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/employing-people%2Fpayroll.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Paying HMRC, employee expenses and benefits and paying staff","short_description":null,"type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=employing-people%2Fpayroll","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/employing-people/payroll"},"parent":{"title":"Employing people","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/employing-people.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Includes pay, contracts and hiring","short_description":null,"type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=employing-people","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/employing-people"},"parent":null}},{"title":"Income Tax","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/tax%2Fincome-tax.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Includes rates and allowances, tax codes and refunds","short_description":null,"type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=tax%2Fincome-tax","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/tax/income-tax"},"parent":{"title":"Money and tax","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/tax.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Includes VAT, debt and inheritance tax","short_description":null,"type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=tax","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/tax"},"parent":null}},{"title":"Expenses and employee benefits","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/business%2Fexpenses-employee-benefits.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Includes company c